<H3> <TI>   Baja California Authorities Investigate Entry of Weapons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baja California Authorities Investigate Entry of Weapons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0506195294 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0506195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Baja California Attorney General's Office is 
investigating the possible entry of a large shipment of weapons 
through the state's border in view of the recent confiscation of 
50 AK-47 rifles in Mexicali. This was disclosed by Baja 
California Governor Ernesto Ruffo Appel in Mexicali. 
  [Begin Ruffo recording] Well, everyone knows that we have 
seized some weapons here. I think we recently seized 
approximately 50 of them. They were apparently part of a larger 
shipment. Therefore, we are investigating. [end recording] 
  According to police, the AK-47 rifles, which were found in a 
clandestine workshop in Mexicali, were modified for automatic 
fire. Ruffo Appel said various police forces and the Army are 
conducting special operations in the state to detect the entry 
of weapons. 

</TEXT>

