<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Candidate Cardenas Receives Death Threat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Candidate Cardenas Receives Death Threat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0506150594 Paris AFP in Spanish 0302 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0506150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 4 Jun (AFP) -- Cuauhtemoc Cardenas, 
center-left presidential candidate, has received an anonymous 
death threat in Oaxaca, in southern Mexico, where he is on a 
campaign tour, the official NOTIMEX news agency reported on 
Saturday. 
  The anonymous threat against Cardenas stated: "We are ready 
to eradicate social blights. Cuauhtemoc Cardenas is one of 
them. Remember what happened to Colosio. Say good-bye to your 
candidate, this week he dies." 
  Colosio, presidential candidate of the Institutional 
Revolutionary Party (PRI), was assassinated on 23 March and 
although the perpetrator was arrested, the motive has yet to be 
clarified. 
  The source indicated that the anonymous threat, which was 
received by the Oaxaca state committee of the Party of the 
Democratic Revolution (PRD, center-left), was sent by an 
organization called Lady of Guadalupe Archdiocesan Sanctuary. 
  At an event in the community of Macuiltianguis, Oaxaca, 
Cardenas scoffed at the threat, indicating that "their bark is 
worse than their bite." He added, "when someone wants to do 
something, he does not announce it. There is nothing to worry 
about." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

