<F P=106> [From the "NTC News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Colombian Foreign Minister Noemi Sanin de Rubio has 
characterized as biased and unfair the gruesome images shown by 
"NTC News" from the video in which Amnesty International 
denounces human rights violations in Colombia. The foreign 
minister said the situations presented in the video cannot be 
considered the result of a premeditated government policy. 
  [Begin Sanin de Rubio recording] I cannot, under any 
circumstance, allow the government to be blamed for this 
violence, these murders, and this so-called social cleansing. I 
cannot agree with that, nor can I believe that everyone in the 
police force is corrupt. [end recording] 
  The foreign minister said that the government's doors are 
open to visits from the international community and that she has 
issued specific instructions to Colombia's ambassadors to invite 
nongovernment human rights organizations to Colombia. 

