<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate Approves Protocol on Illegal Governments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senate Approves Protocol on Illegal Governments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0306132294 Asuncion ULTIMA HORA in Spanish 2 Jun 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> PY0306132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ULTIMA HORA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Senate this morning approved the Washington 
protocol which establishes sanctions against governments 
installed through illegal means. The protocol has been adopted 
by the foreign ministers of OAS country members on behalf of 
their governments. 
  The document sent by the executive branch to the Senate on 
13 
May refers to a modification to the OAS charter. It adds rules 
to protect democratically elected administrations and sanctions 
against those that illegally oust their governors. 
  The senators unanimously approved the protocol. Senator 
Carlos Alberto Gonzalez, head of the Foreign Affairs Committee, 
later emphasized its importance. 
  One sanction contemplated in the document states that 
illegal 
administrations cannot participate in OAS meetings. 
  The Senate also agreed to the executive branch appointment 
of 
Ruben Bareiro Saguier as plenipotentiary ambassador to France. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

