<H3> <TI>   Authorities Fail To Report Incident </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Authorities Fail To Report Incident </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0506031894 Paris AFP in Spanish 0243 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0506031894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 5 Jun (AFP) -- By Saturday night, Cuban 
authorities have still not confirmed reports from the United 
States that 61 Cuban refugees, fleeing Cuba by boat, were 
attacked by Cuban naval vessels, which resulted in the injury of 
seven people. 
  The official Cuban press has still not released any 
information on this new incident, which took place at the same 
time 124 Cubans occupy the Belgian ambassador's residence in 
Havana. 
  According to the passengers rescued south of Florida on 
Saturday by the U.S. Coast Guard, their boat was chased by Cuban 
military vessels following their departure from Mariel (40 km 
west of Havana), and they were fired upon. 
  A coast guard spokesman had not confirmed by Saturday night 
the origin of the shots, stating only that 61 Cubans had been 
rescued from sea and that seven were wounded, four by gunshots. 

</TEXT>

