<H3> <TI>   Two More Cubans Enter Residence </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two More Cubans Enter Residence </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0406033294 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0215 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0406033294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 3 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- Diplomatic sources have 
disclosed that two more Cubans entered the occupied residence of 
the Belgian ambassador in Havana at dawn today. 
  With the new arrivals, the number of occupiers has risen to 
124; they have been at the embassy since 28 May demanding 
permits to leave the country. 
  The sources refrained from specifying how the two new 
arrivals entered the residence, which is surrounded by dozens of 
policemen from the National Revolutionary Police (PNR) and state 
security agents dressed in civilian attire. 
  Today, Willy Verriest, the Belgian Government envoy, 
Ambassador Paul Vermiersch, and Foreign Ministry officials 
examined the "technical aspects of the measures that will be 
adopted to facilitate a final solution" to the problem, 
according to the state-owned news agency PRENSA LATINA. 

</TEXT>

