  [Text] President Alberto Fujimori has left for Tokyo, where 
he will arrive on 5 June. During his stay, Fujimori will meet 
with Emperor Akihito, the Japanese prime minister, foreign 
minister, and other Japanese government officials. 
  Fujimori will stay in Tokyo until Wednesday, 8 June, when he 
will be awarded an honorary degree. From Tokyo, he will depart 
for an official visit to Beijing. During his stay in China, 
Fujimori he will seek a fishing agreement, considering Beijing 
is the main fish meal importer. 

