<F P=102>   PA0506172194 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 2200 GMT 
3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0506172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] An Amnesty International delegation on Friday 
expressed concern about the deterioration of human rights in 
Venezuela, particularly about the questionable activities of 
security forces on the border with Colombia. 
  The delegation led by Mexican Javier Zuniga released the 
results of an extensive investigation of (?prisons), places of 
detention, and torture in general, where flaws in the judicial 
and public security system were evident. The mission also issued 
an alert about the aggressive actions of the Metropolitan Police 
in the application of the vagrants law and about the 
government's proposal to permit citizens to be armed for their 
defense in view of the increasing crime rate. 

