<H3> <TI>   Subcommittee Chairman Endorses Increase </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Subcommittee Chairman Endorses Increase </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0306235594 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0306235594 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Edgar Valle Valle, chairman of the Oil, Energy, and 
Mine Subcommittee of the Chamber of Deputies, has endorsed the 
increase in gasoline prices, saying it is no longer possible to 
continue registering losses in the profit margin of the oil 
sector. Convergence Senator Luis Ramon Matos did not agree, 
saying this is not the opportune time to announce an increase. 
He has said the country is experiencing a devaluation of the 
bolivar, a rise in speculation, price increases, and a 
deterioration in the mass transit system, all of which make 
difficult the acceptance of this decision. 
  According to Consecomercio [National Council of Commerce and 
Services] President Berend Roosen, the reduction in the price of 
the dollar does not entail a reduction in products of mass 
consumption, because most of the raw materials have already been 
imported. He has added a study is being conducted on suggested 
top retail prices to achieve stability between merchants and 
customers. Roosen has recalled that due to the dollar's 
stability, the internal market has been restocked. 

</TEXT>

