BFN 

  [Text] In order to face the sanctions and the total 
embargo, the government has formed a National Crisis Commission. 
By decree, the government of Judge Emile Jonassaint announced 
on Saturday 4 June the formation of a crisis commission in 
charge of managing the embargo and guaranteeing the rights of 
the population to food and work. The commission is also in 
charge of assessing the consequences of the embargo and is 
presided over by the minister of finances and economy. 

