<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Confirms Mexican Prisoner Release </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Confirms Mexican Prisoner Release </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0406165394 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1551 GMT 4 Jun 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA0406165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 4 Jun (PL) -- The Cuban Foreign Ministry 
confirmed today the recent release from prison for humanitarian 
reasons of Mexican citizen Marcelo Garcia Ruvalcaba, who had 
been sentenced by a local court for the crime of terrorism. 
  The foreign minister told PRENSA LATINA that Garcia 
Ruvalcaba 
has a serious kidney problem, and in view of the situation, the 
Cuban Government made the extrajudicial decision to release him 
for humanitarian reasons. 
  The Mexican citizen was sentenced to 10 years in prison by 
the People's Provincial court in this capital on 28 February 
when it was proven that he had brought into the country hand 
grenades and counterrevolutionary pamphlets aimed at carrying 
out terrorist activities. 
  Garcia Ruvalcaba established ties in the Caribbean country 
with individuals hostile to the revolution. He admitted his 
guilt in the public trial attended by representatives of the 
Mexican Embassy and relatives of the defendant. 
  The Mexican citizen is an employee of Continental Airlines 
of 
the United States. He has a residence in Los Angeles where he 
traveled after his release. 
  The Cuban Government's decision on 26 May was previously 
passed to the Mexican Foreign Ministry through the proper 
diplomatic channels. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

