A Network </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Cripton Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Latin American narcotics chiefs agreed to create an 
organization to fight the scourge of drug trafficking, which is 
increasingly more interconnected with another illegal business: 
gunrunning from Europe to Latin America. The decision was 
adopted at a meeting in the Dominican Republic. Here is a 
report by Chelo Garcia: 
  [Begin recording] [Garcia] There is concern that the ties 
between Latin American drug traffickers and gunrunners are 
getting increasingly closer. They work in teams and support 
each other. Sophisticated long- and short-range weapons of 
every caliber, mostly from Europe, are flooding Latin American 
black markets. The Latin American narcotics chiefs decided to 
make efforts to break this deadly alliance during the drug 
summit held in the Dominican Republic. 
  [Colombian counternarcotics chief Colonel Leonardo Gallego] 
The most important things were the plans for new methods and 
means to strengthen this struggle against drug trafficking. 
  [Garcia] It was also proposed at the drug summit that the 
Latin American countries form a single bloc of support to 
control drug cultivation, production, processing, and 
trafficking. They will also work shoulder to shoulder to 
prevent the use of aircraft, vessels, and ground transportation 
to supply materials that Latin American drug traffickers need to 
produce drugs. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

