this fourth version of the Ibero-American summit. [passage 
omited] 
  Shortly before her departure, Comrade Rosa Elena Simeon made 
some statements to the Cuban media delegation, which is here to 
assess the event and its topics. Here is a small fragment of 
Comrade Rosa Elena Simeon's statement: 
  [Begin Simeon recording] Emphasis has been placed on 
something throughout the debate and the three roundtables: 
Research work must be guaranteed sustained financing. What do 
we call sustained financing per se? We mean it must have 
continuity. That is the experience in our country, which today 
invests $25 per inhabitant. The revolution has made an 
extraordinary effort in the formation of human resources 
throughout the history of the revolution and today we can enjoy 
the results. You cannot invest in the research sector and then 
fail to give it continuity. That investment is not recovered in 
the short term. This entails medium term and long term 
investments. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

