<H3> <TI>   Camaguey Province Resumes Sugarcane Harvest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Camaguey Province Resumes Sugarcane Harvest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0606163894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1640 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0606163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Manuel Cano Iglesias from Camaguey Province for </F>
the "Doing Radio" newscast] 
  [Text] We would like to report the sugar harvest resumed in 
Camaguey Province when the Noel Fernandez Central's machinery 
was started in Minas Municipality. The central's mills were 
started after the recent torrential and extended rains. The 
central will also receive raw material from areas around the 
Brazil and Sierra de Cubitas Centrals, and zones where the rain 
has not delayed the harvest so much. 
  Within the strategy, work is also underway in complexes 
located in the central and southern part of the province. Some 
of them will thus participate in the mill work by receiving 
sugarcane from their own areas and from neighboring areas. 
Within the principle of cutting sugarcane wherever possible and 
sending it to whichever central can mill it, Camaguey sugarcane 
workers have resumed the harvest operations because they are 
aware of the importance of contributing as much as they can for 
the country's economy. 

</TEXT>

