<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reina Distressed Over More Drastic Measures Against Haiti </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reina Distressed Over More Drastic Measures Against Haiti </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0606165694 Tegucigalpa LA TRIBUNA in Spanish 4 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PA0606165694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tegucigalpa LA TRIBUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Although some ships fly the Honduran flag, this 
does not necessarily mean they are Honduran, President Carlos 
Roberto Reina said yesterday in reference to the report that 
Honduran-flagged ships have violated the embargo against Haiti. 
  He considered it distressing and unfortunate that the United 
States and the inter-American system are about to adopt more 
drastic measures to reestablish democracy in Haiti. He also 
announced this topic will be addressed at the summit in 
Cartagena de Indias, Colombia. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

