<F P=100> SOUTH AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duhalde Willing To Run on Ticket </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duhalde Willing To Run on Ticket </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0606200094 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1926 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0606200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 4 Jun (NA) -- Buenos Aires Province 
Governor Eduardo Duhalde stated on 4 June that he is convinced 
that the provincial Constituent Assembly will approve the bill 
allowing Buenos Aires governors to be reelected. He made it 
clear, however, that if that is not the case, he is willing to 
be Menem's running mate in the 1995 presidential elections. 
  Speaking in San Vicente, Duhalde said he does not want the 
people of Buenos Aires Province to push for his reelection 
because this issue will be negotiated at the provincial 
Constituent Assembly. 

</TEXT>

