<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shining Path Attempt To Murder Former President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shining Path Attempt To Murder Former President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0606183094 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1321 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY0606183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lima, 6 Jun (EFE) -- The Lima daily EXPRESO reported 
on 6 June that the police have thwarted an attempt by the maoist 
Shining Path [SL] gang to kill former Peruvian President 
Fernando Belaunde Terry (1980-1985). 
  EXPRESO reported that a man known as "Comrade Jonas" was 
arrested some 100 meters from the podium from which Belaunde 
Terry was addressing a rally at the main square in Huaraz, 
capital of Ancash Department in the northern Andean region. The 
arrested man was carrying a long-range weapon fitted with a 
silencer. 
  "Comrade Jonas" allegedly confessed that his mission was to 
"eliminate" the leaders of Popular Action, the party that 
Belaunde Terry founded and leads. 
  The police reported that three other SL members were 
arrested 
in Yungay, also in Ancash Department. 
  According to EXPRESO "Comrade Jonas" was involved in the 
murder of two Polish priests in May 1993 in Pariacoto, Ancash 
Department. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

