<H3> <TI>   Only 3 State-Owned Companies' Officials Dismissed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Only 3 State-Owned Companies' Officials Dismissed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0606185594 Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO in Portuguese 2315 GMT 
3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0606185594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brasilia, 3 Jun (AE) -- Today, one of President 
Itamar Franco's advisers reported that political pressure on 
Planalto Palace and several ministries has reduced to only three 
the number of state-owned companies' directors who were 
dismissed for converting employees' salaries into Real Value 
Units by the maximum percentage index. Transportation Minister 
Rubem Bayma Denys had estimated that at least 50 managers would 
be dismissed, discharged, or retired as a result of the 
incident. The official gazette, however, only published the name 
of three directors to be dismissed: Rilson Carneiro Raposo, Jose 
Eudes Rangel, and Roberto Vaz da Silva. They are, respectively, 
the president and directors of the Executive Group for the Study 
of Transportation Integration Policy (Geipot). [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

