<H3> <TI>   Franco To Open 24th OAS General Assembly in Belem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Franco To Open 24th OAS General Assembly in Belem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0606125594 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 1000 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0606125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Luiz Augusto Mendonca from Belem -- live] </F>
  [Text] President Itamar Franco arrived in Belem [Para 
State] on the night of 5 June. This morning at 1000 [1400 GMT], 
he will officially open the 24th OAS General Assembly. The 
president of the Republic was welcomed at the Belem Air Base by 
Para Governor Carlos Santos on the night of 5 June and 
immediately left for the Hilton Hotel, where he is staying. 
  After opening the OAS meeting, President Franco will visit 
the (Emilio Goeldi) Museum in Belem where he will plant a tree 
to celebrate the International Environment Day. Franco will 
then hear speeches by the ministers of the environment and Legal 
Amazon Region, and science and technology. Franco will issue a 
stamp celebrating International Environment Day. 
  In the afternoon, President Itamar Franco will have a 
private 
meeting with ousted Haitian President Jean-Bertrand Aristide. 
At night, the president of the Republic will be decorated with 
the Grao Para medal, the most important Para State decoration. 
He will later host a dinner for the foreign delegations. 

</TEXT>

