<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Signs Accord To Exchange Military Attaches </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Signs Accord To Exchange Military Attaches </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0706003694 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2200 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0706003694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Antonia Marcia Vale from Belem, </F>
Para State] 
  [Text] Brazilian Foreign Minister Celso Amorim and Russian 
Deputy Foreign Minister Georgiy Mamedov have signed an agreement 
to exchange military attaches between the two countries. 
Mamedov, who is attending the 24th OAS General Assembly as an 
observer, stated that the agreement does not entail any form of 
ideological agreement, but rather stems from mutually 
advantageous relations. 
  Mamedov said Russia and Brazil are following the same path 
toward promoting democratization in the world. He described 
Brazil as a priority partner for Russia. He noted that the 
agreement will pave the way for implementing several cooperation 
projects between the Russian and Brazilian Armed Forces, in 
addition to promoting the transfer of technology. 
  The agreement may also be instrumental in improving the 
bilateral trade balance, which last year stood at $300 million. 
Foreign Ministry experts consider this figure to be well below 
the potential for trade between the two countries. Foreign 
Minister Amorim will visit the Russian Federation in December to 
sign new agreements. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

