<F P=100> INTER-AMERICAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paraguayan Minister Urges Increased Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paraguayan Minister Urges Increased Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0806022994 Asuncion ULTIMA HORA in Spanish 7 Jun 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> PY0806022994 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ULTIMA HORA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning during his speech at the 24th OAS 
General Assembly in Belem do Para, Brazil, Paraguayan Foreign 
Minister Luis Maria Ramirez Boettner asked the rich countries to 
increase their cooperation with poor countries to fight poverty 
and seek development. Addressing the other OAS foreign 
ministers, the Paraguayan foreign minister also endorsed the 
enhancement, development, and progress of the democratic system 
in all the American countries. 
  Ramirez Boettner criticized the gap between rich and poor 
countries, claiming that after the end of the Cold War, world 
assistance funds to overcome poverty and seek development have 
become increasingly scarce and inaccessible. Ramirez Boettner 
emphasized: "And it is surprisingly paradoxical that, when the 
new international order makes clamorous announcements of an era 
of international cooperation and solidarity, there actually are 
so many symptoms of a growing and fragmentary isolationism 
between the rich and the poor." 
  Ramirez Boettner then asked for increased cooperation 
between 
rich and poor countries for the sake of the development and 
well-being of most countries. He added that international aid 
to enhance democracy and reduce poverty "has become elusive and 
preconditioned." 
<H5>  Democracy for All </H5>
  In his message to the OAS foreign ministers' meeting, 
Ramirez 
Boettner deplored the fact that democracy has not reached all 
American countries and that there still are exceptions. Ramirez 
Boettner said: "All of us want all our American brothers to 
equally join in democratic development and progress, with the 
restoration of all liberties." 
  In order to receive more technical and financial assistance 
from the "rich" countries, the foreign minister pointed out that 
it is necessary for American countries to close ranks and raise 
in successive meetings the hopes of the poorest countries. 
  In his message to the OAS General Assembly, the Paraguayan 
foreign minister asked that the Inter-American System be 
enhanced and strengthened. 
<H5>  Will Return Tomorrow </H5>
  After participating in the 24th OAS General Assembly in this 
Brazilian city, Ramirez Boettner will return to our country at 
1050 on 8 June. On 9 June, Ramirez Boettner will join President 
Wasmosy on a visit to Montevideo, Uruguay, to dedicate the 
dredging of the Martin Garcia channel. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

