  [Text] In Port-au-Prince, the provisional government 
protested against statements made by President Bill Clinton of 
the United States. The government of Judge Emile Jonassaint 
raised a vigorous protest against President Clinton's recent 
statements, according to which Haiti is located in the United 
States' backyard. 
  Such untimely statements clearly violate the cardinal and 
universal principles of sovereignty and self-determination that 
govern relations among nations, writes the Ministry of 
Information in a press release. The land of Haiti is not and 
will never be the backyard of any state, not even of the world's 
most powerful, continues the government press release which also 
denounces the unspeakable behavior of unnatural sons of the 
homeland who, obsessed with the passion of power, offer the 
country's detractors an opportunity to degrade it. 

</TEXT>

