<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   PGR Arrests 13 for Gun Running; Weapons Seized </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PGR Arrests 13 for Gun Running; Weapons Seized </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0606153794 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0606153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Attorney General's Office [PGR] reported that 13 
gun runners were arrested in several operations. At the same 
time, 10,159 ammunition rounds of diverse caliber, 550 grams of 
dynamite, and 17 weapons were seized. The PGR reported that the 
operations are continuing in order to determine the origin and 
final destination of the weapons as well as possible 
participation of other individuals in the gun running activity. 
The PGR indicated that the largest weapons' seizure took place 
at the Sonora checkpoint, where 7,600 ammunition rounds of 
various calibers and seven weapons were confiscated. 

</TEXT>

