<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Endara Issues Pardons for Political Crimes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Endara Issues Pardons for Political Crimes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0806001294 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0806001294 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "RPC Television News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Guillermo Endara Galimany today, utilizing 
his constitutional powers, pardoned a number of individuals 
accused of allegedly committing political crimes. 
  Among those pardoned are former President Eric Arturo 
Delvalle and the 510 corregimiento representatives who appointed 
Francisco Rodriguez as president for the presidential term that 
started on 1 September 1989. Also included in this pardon 
granted to those who committed only political crimes are 
Benjamin Colamarco Patino; Arturo Diez; Rafael Arosemena; 
Orville K. Goodin; Olmedo David Miranda; Nander Pitty Velasquez; 
Jorge Eduardo Ritter; Marta Amado Trevia; Manuel Solis Palma; 
Francisco Sanchez Cardenas; Julio Shaik; and Jaime Simmons. 
  Meanwhile, Tomas Gabriel Altamirano Duque, who allegedly 
slandered and offended Omayra Correa by publishing three 
political cartoons in LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA in August and 
September 1989, was also granted a pardon. Others who were 
granted presidential pardons include journalists Escolastico 
Calvo and Guillermo Keevers. 
  These pardons fail to absolve these people from being 
prosecuted for committing common crimes, however. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

