<F P=102>   PA0806011794 </F>
<F P=103> PA0806011794 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Colombian economic developments monitored through 7 
June. 
  The Agriculture and Livestock Marketing Institute has 
announced that it will buy the entire rice crop of 45,000 tons 
in Ariari, Meta Department, where the Guillermo Leon Valencia 
Bridge collapsed, leaving the area cut off from the rest of the 
nation. It is possible that the government might also purchase 
the corn crop. (Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Canal A 
Network in Spanish 1730 GMT 31 May 94) 
  The National Administrative Department of Statistics [DANE] 
has reported that inflation reached 1.53 percent in May, adding 
that for the first five months of the year, overall inflation is 
running at 13.65 percent. DANE statistics indicate that the May 
inflation rate was driven higher in part by rent increases. 
Pasto was the most expensive city, while Monteria was the least 
expensive in the same month. (Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision 
Television Canal A Network in Spanish 0000 GMT 2 Jun 94) 

</TEXT>

