<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Denies Pinochet Traveling Under False ID </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Denies Pinochet Traveling Under False ID </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0706164594 Santiago LA TERCERA DE LA HORA in Spanish 31 
May 94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PY0706164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago LA TERCERA DE LA HORA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Army has categorically denied that its 
commander in chief, Captain General Augusto Pinochet Ugarte, is 
traveling with a false passport "because he is traveling with an 
official passport issued by the Chilean Government to public 
authorities fulfilling official duties abroad." As for reports 
that Pinochet had to hastily check out of a hotel in the 
Netherlands, the Army stated through a communique that the 
reports "are inaccurate" because the high-ranking official "has 
fulfilled the scheduled itinerary without any changes." 
  The Army communique ends by stating that in Prague, capital 
of the Czech Republic, Gen. Pinochet was received by Chilean 
Ambassador Rolando Stein and the Omnipol Company president, who 
held a reception in his honor. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

