<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ex-Sandinist Soldiers Occupy Venezuelan Embassy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ex-Sandinist Soldiers Occupy Venezuelan Embassy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0706224194 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 2155 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0706224194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Managua, 7 Jun (DPA) -- Approximately 30 former 
Sandinist soldiers occupied the Venezuelan Embassy in Managua 
this afternoon (local time), allegedly as a pressure tactic for 
social and economic benefits from the administration of Violeta 
Chamorro. 
  Initial reports indicate the occupiers, former Government 
Ministry employees, were unarmed when they entered the embassy, 
which is located approximately 10 km south of Managua in the 
luxurious sector of Sierras de Santo Domingo. 
  Nicaraguan Foreign Ministry spokesmen say they have not 
received official information regarding the occupation, and 
Venezuelan Ambassador Juan Jose Monsant has not disclosed the 
demands of the former soldiers. 
  Dozens of policemen have been deployed to the area 
surrounding the Venezuelan Embassy. 

</TEXT>

