<H3> <TI>   Radio Cites Calls for OAS Reintegration Study </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Cites Calls for OAS Reintegration Study </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0806175094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0806175094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Exclusive" program] </F>
  [Text] The 24th OAS General Assembly today continued 
hearing requests for Cuba's reintegration into that regional 
organization, from which it was separated in 1962 because of its 
political differences with the United States. On the second day 
of sessions in Belem do Para, Brazilian Foreign Minister Celso 
Amorim spoke of Cuba's reintegration into the OAS Assembly and 
insisted on the need to reevaluate Cuba's situation within the 
hemispheric community. Outgoing OAS President Joao Baena Soares, 
as well as Brazilian President Itamar Franco, recommended during 
last night's inaugural meeting that Cuba's reintegration be 
studied. This topic was not on the agenda of the meeting, which 
will conclude on 10 June. 

</TEXT>

