<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Companies Discover Cardenas Bay Deposit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0806174994 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0806174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "First Thing" program] </F>
  [Text] The first well drilled by oil companies working with 
Cupet [expansion unknown] in the search for new deposits has 
yielded positive results. A deposit has been discovered with 
research currently underway to determine its dimensions. GRANMA 
reports that the discovery was made at Cardenas Bay, Matanzas 
Province, in the area leased by Canadian companies Canada 
Northwest Energy and Fortuna Petroleum, Inc. Tests reveal an 
estimated daily production of 3,750 barrels of 16 API -- the 
international unit to measure the oil's density -- oil. The oil 
is considered heavy but of better quality than the oil extracted 
at Varadero. 

</TEXT>

