    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on criminal activity monitored from Havana radio sources 
in Spanish between 26 May and 5 June. 
  The Havana police have arrested a group of thieves, who were 
prepared to steal parabolic antennas and automobile batteries in 
Diez de Octubre Municipality, Havana City Province. Batteries 
and antennas were repossessed from the people who purchased them 
from the group to manufacture generators. Seven suspects are 
currently in jail awaiting trial. (Radio Progreso Network in 
Spanish 1100 GMT 26 May) 
  "A total of 415 violators of the self-employment law have 
been fined in Matanzas Province to date. A total of 200 of the 
fined citizens in Varadero are from other provinces." (Radio 
Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 GMT 3 June) 

