<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   CCD Approves Privatizing Hydroelectric Plants </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CCD Approves Privatizing Hydroelectric Plants </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0806155494 Lima LA REPUBLICA in Spanish 28 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PY0806155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima LA REPUBLICA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The official bloc of the CCD [Democratic 
Constituent Congress] on 27 May approved the bill that includes 
special, agricultural, and hydroelectric projects in the 
privatization process, disregarding the opposition's warning. 
  Therefore, large hydroelectric projects such as Olmos, 
Chavimochic, Majes, Tinajones, and Jequetepeque-Zana; the San 
Lorenzo irrigation project; and the Huinco and Marcapomacocha 
Machu Pichu hydroelectric plants, among others, can be sold. 
  The organizations, production units, and other projects 
under 
the state's responsibility also can be sold. 
  The new law that changes Legislative Decree No. 674 for 
Promoting Private Investments in State Enterprises also grants 
full powers to the Privatization Commission (Copri) to carry out 
the auctions. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

