<H3> <TI>   Dominican Official Terms Embargo `Genocide' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dominican Official Terms Embargo `Genocide' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0806215494 Port-au-Prince Radio Tropic FM in French 1400 
GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0806215494 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Tropic FM </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] To avoid genocide in Haiti, it is urgent the United 
Nations send the Dominican Republic the list of food products 
not included in the embargo. This is the position expressed on 7 
June by Dominican Deputy Foreign Minister Fabio Herrera Cabral. 
In his opinion, the complete closing of the border between the 
two countries is speeding up an imposed, strategic genocide 
within Haitian society. 
  Cabral also complains that he has not yet received the list 
promised about one week ago by Dante Caputo. The deputy foreign 
minister also pointed out that he does not know the date on 
which to expect the mission of 60 UN observers who have agreed 
to help with surveillance of the border area. 

</TEXT>

