<H3> <TI>   Sanguinetti, Batalla Set Basis for Electoral Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanguinetti, Batalla Set Basis for Electoral Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0706175594 Montevideo EL PAIS in Spanish 2 Jun 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> PY0706175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Montevideo EL PAIS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] During a ceremony at List 2000 [not further 
specified] headquarters at midday on 1 June, Julio Maria 
Sanguinetti, leader of the Batlleist Forum [Colorado Party 
faction], and Senator Hugo Batalla, leader of the Party of the 
Government by the People, were presented with a document 
containing the programmatic bases of an electoral agreement 
between both political movements. 
  Flanked by Hugo Fernandez Faingold and Heber Gatto, 
Sanguinetti and Batalla each delivered a short speech on the 
agreement's implications to an audience of more than 100 people, 
including leaders and experts from both movements. [passage 
omitted] 
  Sanguinetti said: "What nurtures this agreement is a 
reflection and an analysis of the country and its future." 
  He added that it was with this objective in mind that he 
started to negotiate with Sen. Hugo Batalla, and stated that he 
was confident that talks would be brought to a successful 
conclusion in the coming weeks. [passage omitted] 

