<H3> <TI>   Cuba's Castro Congratulates FSLN's D. Ortega </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cuba's Castro Congratulates FSLN's D. Ortega </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0906045094 Managua BARRICADA in Spanish 7 Jun 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PA0906045094 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua BARRICADA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Letter of congratulations from Cuban President Fidel Castro </F>
to Daniel Ortega, secretary general of the Nicaraguan Sandinist 
National Liberation Front, FSLN, dated 24 May] 
  [Text] Havana, 24 May 1994, 36th year of the revolution. 
  Comrade Daniel Ortega Saavedra 
  Secretary General 
  Sandinist National Liberation Front 
  Dear Daniel: 
  Allow me to express my most fraternal congratulations for 
your recent election as FSLN secretary general. 
  The special congress that recently ended was, undoubtedly, 
an 
expression of maturity, particularly of the unity preserved by 
that political organization during the most difficult stages of 
struggle through which it has historically journeyed. 
  That event blazes a path of hope for the organization in its 
continuous efforts to accomplish the objectives of genuine and 
full social justice, results to which it has committed decades 
of struggle, as well as the valuable blood of its martyrs. 
  Under international circumstances as complex as the present, 
where a unipolar world under the hegemony of the United States 
has taken shape, the will, fortitude for struggle, and faith in 
the people's victory is tested. 
  I would like to convey my congratulations to all the comrade 
delegates to the congress, the Sandinist Assembly, and the 
elected National Directorate. 
  An embrace, 
  [Signed] Fidel Castro Ruz. 

</TEXT>

