<H3> <TI>   PFCRN Deputy Candidate Reportedly Murdered </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PFCRN Deputy Candidate Reportedly Murdered </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0906025394 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0052 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0906025394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Aide Cedeno in Michoacan from the "Panorama </F>
Newscast" -- live] 
  [Text] Federal deputy candidate Margarito Manrique Saucedo, 
of the Cardenist Front for National Reconstruction Party [PFCRN] 
in Tacambaro district, died in a traffic accident earlier today, 
just 72 days before the federal election, announced Luis 
Martinez Cetina, president of the PFCRN National Executive 
Committee, charging Manrique, 36, had been murdered, as 
everything indicated he had been intentionally run down. 
  Luis Martinez said the alleged accident occurred in 
(Huatano), Michoacan, where the deceased was campaigning. As 
the candidate crossed a road, an unidentified pickup truck ran 
him down, killing him. Luis Martinez announced his party 
expects a thorough investigation of the facts and will demand 
justice. So far, no one has been identified as the alleged 
perpetrator or perpetrators of this crime, which occurred just 
hours ago. 

</TEXT>

