<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   President-Elect Wants `Adjustment' of Foreign Debt Payments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President-Elect Wants `Adjustment' of Foreign Debt Payments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0906044994 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0906044994 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Fernando Fernandez from the "RPC Television News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] President-elect Ernesto Perez Balladares has stated 
that it is unfair for the incoming administration to have to pay 
for the current government's inability to meet its obligations 
with the international financial institutions [IFI's]. 
  The president-elect made his statements following a meeting 
with recently elected PRD [Revolutionary Democratic Party] 
legislators and members of the future cabinet, who will take 
office as of 1 September. The meeting was designed to 
coordinate future government policies between the executive and 
judicial branches during the transition period. 
  According to Perez Balladares, the government's announced 
budget cuts should not affect the incoming administration. 
  [Begin Perez Balladares recording] I believe it is unfair 
that our incoming administration should be the one to pay for 
the current administration's inability to meet its debt 
obligations. In this respect, it seems to me that the best 
approach would be to meet with the IFI's and agree on an 
adjustment and reform program that takes into account the 
nation's social needs. I am quite sure Planning Minister 
Guillermo Chapman is of the same opinion and will discuss the 
issue with the IFI's in due time. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

