<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Finance Minister Reaches Agreement With Farmers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finance Minister Reaches Agreement With Farmers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0906023194 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 2300 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0906023194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Rubens Ricupero has announced new 
decisions regarding the real currency. Ricupero, who met with 
the Chamber of Deputies Economy Committee, came to seek 
guarantees that farmers would continue to produce food. Today 
it was agreed that the government will renegotiate the farmers' 
debts, and give them up to 10 years to repay. The government 
will likewise pay the overdue farming insurance debts and 
suspend for three months the Bank of Brazil lawsuits against 
farmers in arrears. 
  During a luncheon with commerce representatives, Ricupero 
explained the implementation of the new currency. During this 
luncheon he gave advance notice of some of the points of the 
economic plan: 
  Credits: The government will not adopt any measure to reduce 
consumption of goods like cars and household appliances. 
  Interest rates: They will continue to be high until the 
economy reaches stability. 
  Contracts: Those in real cruzeiros will be converted into 
URV's [real value units] based on the URV rate of 1 July. 
  Ufir [Reference Fiscal Unit]: It will not be abolished. It 
will continue to index income tax paid in advance and overdue 
taxes. 
  Postdated checks: Banks will accept checks written in real 
cruzeiros until 1 August. 

</TEXT>

