<F P=100> INTER-AMERICAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   OAS Meeting Views Haiti Sanctions, Other Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    OAS Meeting Views Haiti Sanctions, Other Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Next OAS General Assembly To Be in Haiti </H4>

<F P=102> PY0906231394 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2200 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0906231394 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Antonia Marcia Vale from Belem, Para State] </F>
  [Text] The OAS will hold its next general assembly in 
Port-au-Prince, the capital city of Haiti. The decision was 
made today at a plenary session of the OAS General Assembly in 
Belem by all of the 34 OAS member countries. 
  Haiti has been ruled by a military dictatorship since 1991, 
when Army coupists ousted the first elected president since the 
downfall of a previous dictatorship that had lasted 
approximately 50 years. 
  OAS Secretary General Joao Baena Soares has described the 
OAS 
General Assembly's decision as unequivocal proof of a clear 
political will to resolve the Haitian crisis. In his opinion, 
the holding of the general assembly in Haiti will be 
instrumental in confirming the restoration of democracy in that 
country. 

</TEXT>

